  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Due to https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/34160, we may see pods which have their `DeletionTimeStamp` set and surface in kubectl as Terminating whose status is simply unknown because the node/kubelet was unresponsive for sometime. We should do a better job of surfacing this to the user. \n\nFor example:\n\n```\n$ kubectl get pods\nNAME       READY     STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE\nalpine-0   1/1       Running   0          29m\nalpine-1   1/1       Lost      1          17h\n```\n\n`kubectl describe` on the lost pod should ideally have a longer message that the node it was running on has not responded in a certain amount of time.\n\ncc @erictune @kow3ns @kubernetes/sig-apps \n",
  "closed_at": "2016-11-04T01:05:44Z",
